      "updated": 1777242467586,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Class GameObject -> base class for all game objects.\nImplements load_image to loading the child object \nimages, rect that returns the rect from the objects and\ndraw, which draws the object.\n\nClass Player -> player class. To instantiate, takes the\nargument 'game', from main.py, where it is instantiated.\nAlso has a position attribute, and PLAYER_SPEED.\nHas the move() method, which allows movement in the\nexplore mode of the game. \nTODO: bring the notes definition to this class for\nplaying the notes in the explore part of the game.\n\nClass Staff -> Object from the BattleEvent. Holds the\nnotes to be played and the moving buttons which tells\nwhich key has to be pressed. Receives the argument\ngame, being instantiated in the events.py file. Extends\nthe GameObject draw() method to draw the buttons\nof each note.\n\nClass Button -> buttons of the battle event which \nshows the notes to be played.\n\nClass MovingBlock -> represents the objects that \nappear during the battle event that indicates which \nbuttons need to be pressed. To instantiate, receive \nthe arguments game, target_button(the corresponding\nnote from the Button class), and note_key, which will\napply sharps or flats to the free keys press, allowing\nmusical key changes.\n\nClass KeyChangeMarker -> A visual indication of key \nchanges that happens in the middle of songs.\n\nClass NPCGeneric -> Holds the mandatory attributes\nand methods for NPCs. NPCs will all inherit from this\nclass. To instantiate, requires: game, name, sprite_path,\ndialogues, song_key, health, battle_intro and \nbattle_outro.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 19.028338790651038,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Class GameObject -> base class for all game objects.\nImplements load_image to loading the child object \nimages, rect that returns the rect from the objects and\ndraw, which draws the object.\n\nClass Player -> player class. To instantiate, takes the\nargument 'game', from main.py, where it is instantiated.\nAlso has a position attribute, and PLAYER_SPEED.\nHas the move() method, which allows movement in the\nexplore mode of the game. \nTODO: bring the notes definition to this class for\nplaying the notes in the explore part of the game.\n\nClass Staff -> Object from the BattleEvent. Holds the\nnotes to be played and the moving buttons which tells\nwhich key has to be pressed. Receives the argument\ngame, being instantiated in the events.py file. Extends\nthe GameObject draw() method to draw the buttons\nof each note.\n\nClass Button -> buttons of the battle event which \nshows the notes to be played.\n\nClass MovingBlock -> represents the objects that \nappear during the battle event that indicates which \nbuttons need to be pressed. To instantiate, receive \nthe arguments game, target_button(the corresponding\nnote from the Button class), and note_key, which will\napply sharps or flats to the free keys press, allowing\nmusical key changes.\n\nClass KeyChangeMarker -> A visual indication of key \nchanges that happens in the middle of songs.\n\nClass NPCGeneric -> Holds the mandatory attributes\nand methods for NPCs. NPCs will all inherit from this\nclass. To instantiate, requires: game, name, sprite_path,\ndialogues, song_key, health, battle_intro and \nbattle_outro.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
