    {
      "id": "4P7CpbiGorYRUE8VBLurn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -960.3085836206184,
      "y": -1515.6906745423448,
      "width": 503.15447998046875,
      "height": 642.2064341844725,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "hsz4vRw9aaaiqtupzHufI"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1732496544,
      "version": 4696,
      "versionNonce": 693261472,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777243367571,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Handles sound creation/play through load_sound,\ngenerate_sound and generate_distorted_sound.\nThe first loads from files; in case it fails, generates\nsound from the second function, which uses numpy. \nThe distorted sound function creates sound to be \nplayed when a key is pressef without a moving block \ncolliding with it to highlight that the key press was\nunsucessful.\nThe get_modifier_color_overlay switches the light\nfrom the moving blocks, making it lighter if the \ncoming block is a sharp or darker if is a flat, providing\nthe equivalent symbol to be drawn aswell.\n\nClass BattleEvent -> Handles the heart of the \ngameplay, dealing with drawing the Battle event \nobjects, appluing the logic, playing the sounds,\nkeeping track of score and adjusting the gameplay\nfor the chosen difficulty.\n\nClass TalkEvent -> TODO: this class would deal with \nhandling player interaction with NPCs, especially the\nconversation. Need consideration if it might be better\nto just implement the talks as a method for \nNPCGeneric.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 19.028338790651038,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Handles sound creation/play through load_sound,\ngenerate_sound and generate_distorted_sound.\nThe first loads from files; in case it fails, generates\nsound from the second function, which uses numpy. \nThe distorted sound function creates sound to be \nplayed when a key is pressef without a moving block \ncolliding with it to highlight that the key press was\nunsucessful.\nThe get_modifier_color_overlay switches the light\nfrom the moving blocks, making it lighter if the \ncoming block is a sharp or darker if is a flat, providing\nthe equivalent symbol to be drawn aswell.\n\nClass BattleEvent -> Handles the heart of the \ngameplay, dealing with drawing the Battle event \nobjects, appluing the logic, playing the sounds,\nkeeping track of score and adjusting the gameplay\nfor the chosen difficulty.\n\nClass TalkEvent -> TODO: this class would deal with \nhandling player interaction with NPCs, especially the\nconversation. Need consideration if it might be better\nto just implement the talks as a method for \nNPCGeneric.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
