      "updated": 1777244818165,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "TODOs: \n* Create dialogues in dialogues.py - Subtask from creating the story\n* Create new maps in maps.py\n* Draw the maps (currently, only background1.png exists, a placeholder)\n* Create NPCS and their pictures\n* Implement map change (there is a function in main.py, need to implement within the game logic)\n* Create saving and loading\n* Create new songs\n* Consider some way to improve the music gameplay, the current is restrictive as sharps,flats and naturals can't be mixed unless a key change happens\n* Implement some sort of progression system, such as an rpg-like stats, fame or similar\n* Implement some sort of money system to eventually allow buying different instruments\n* Implement the music-lesson type of battle event",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "TODOs: \n* Create dialogues in dialogues.py - Subtask from creating the story\n* Create new maps in maps.py\n* Draw the maps (currently, only background1.png exists, a placeholder)\n* Create NPCS and their pictures\n* Implement map change (there is a function in main.py, need to implement within the game logic)\n* Create saving and loading\n* Create new songs\n* Consider some way to improve the music gameplay, the current is restrictive as sharps,flats and naturals can't be mixed unless a key change happens\n* Implement some sort of progression system, such as an rpg-like stats, fame or similar\n* Implement some sort of money system to eventually allow buying different instruments\n* Implement the music-lesson type of battle event",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
